en_753718_0	Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, Commander of the Army as the Chief Guest together with Mrs Chandrika Senanayake, President, Army Seva Vanitha Unit (ASVU) attended the 'Poson Bethigee' (devotional songs) organized by the Sri Lanka Signal Corps (SLSC) Seva Vanitha Unit on the theme ‘Poson Buddhabhi Wandana’ on Poson Full Moon Poya Day (16) at Sri Bodhirajaramaya Panagoda.
en_753718_1	Major General Nilantha Hettiarachchi, Colonel Commandant, SLSC and Chief Signal Officer welcomed the Commander of the Army at the venue together with Major General Sathyapriya Liyanage, Commander, Security Forces - West.
en_753718_2	Members of the SLSC Army personnel sang devotional songs and paid their homage to the memory of Arahath Mahinda during the presentation.
en_753718_3	At the end of the event Mrs Chandrika Senanayake, President, ASVU presented gifts to the participants for their contribution.
en_753718_4	Performances followed a group photograph with the Commander of the Army and Mrs Senanayake.
en_753718_5	Major General Sathyapriya Liyanage, Commander, Security Forces - West, Major General Pooraka Senevirathna, Director, Directorate of Quality Assurance and Inspection (DQAI), Major General C.M.D.P Chandrasekara, Director General Army Quartering and Real Estates, Mrs Keshani Hettiarachchi, Chairperson, SLSC Seva Vanitha Unit, Senior Officers, Officers, Spouses and Other Ranks attended the event.
